originalText.text: Sean is an incredibly knowledgable and inspiring coach! After just one session, I walked away with a long list of goals, tips, and new knowledge about running that I know will benefit my practice now and in the future. I'd love to work with him more! Sean is warm and encouraging, but is also clearly a true expert in his field. I felt very lucky to learn from him, and I know others would also be fortunate to do the same! If you need top-notch coaching, go with Central Park Coaching!

originalText.text:
If there is one thing I miss about NYC its my running in Central Park with Sean Fortune , Central Park Coaching as my running coach. Sean is a fantastic , educated running coach,  and trainer that understands each individuals capacity as a runner.  He understands  and educates on body mechanics,  There were times when I felt certain goals were impossible… but Sean helped me realize, that If I dug deep enough and believed, the times and paces I thought were out of my reach were attainable.
He helped me tap into my speed.. since he saw I am a better short  distance runner, with capability for speed at my age, but understood I love the long run, and marathon training.
Happily, Central Park Coaching is now coming to Miami as SouthBeach Coaching..
so excited!

originalText.text: I have loved working with Sean for the last 12 months. His thoughtful workout routines and flexibility given my work and family commitments have been revolutionary for me. I bettered my PR in the New York Marathon by over 1 hour through my work with him, and generally feel like a more informed and healthier athlete. I could not recommend him more highly!

originalText.text: Sean is an amazing coach! He not only thrives to push your limits but does so holistically: just improving your fitness is not enough, the diet, the sleeping, the intensity, duration, and frequency of runs, and many other things all come into play to reach your running goals and Sean's expertise on the whole process is remarkable. My son's heavy schedule unfortunately is not allowing him to see Sean as often as we would want, but even so Sean knows how to customize the sessions to get the best out of them. Thank you Sean!

originalText.text: Sean Fortune’s run coaching helped me achieve a personal record in my 2023 NYC marathon! I am grateful for his practical advice and training sessions over 6 months along with tips on nutrition, injury prevention, stretching, gear and race day fuel. He also has an optimistic outlook which is helpful.  I highly recommend Sean to anyone who wants to put in the time and work to achieve a great running race, and enjoy the process!
